    "This means that the outcomes of previous learning iterations influence subsequent ones, leading to an increase in the importance of data over boosting rounds.",
    "AdaBoost, a specific boosting algorithm, focuses on increasing the weight of training samples that were poorly predicted by the previous model.",
    "Initially, AdaBoost creates the first weak learner and assigns output weight (C) and model weight (w) to each data point based on the learning results.",
    "The model is then updated with the data weights.",
    "This process is repeated for a specified number of iterations (N)."
